      "note": "SocialMediaOS Content Intelligence API (Priority Ideas subset). Built by the loop (queued smos-intel-routes); imports the four intel services (title-universe, script-scorer, publish-gate, repurpose) and exposes /api/v1/marketing/intel/*. Mounted here so the functional-proof gate verifies the endpoints are LIVE before the step can be done. Records a benign 'module not found' health error until the loop ships the file — fail-open, never blocks boot."
    },
    {
      "path": "routes/lifeos-phase2-routes.js",
      "register": "registerLifeosPhase2Routes",
      "enabled": true,
      "note": "LifeOS Phase 2 REST surface. Was blocked forever because s07 (auto-register) depended on s06 while s06 failed module-health for missing auto-register — chicken-egg. Mounted here so functional-proof can pass and the loop can finish Phase 2."
    },
    {
      "path": "routes/lifeos-phase3-routes.js",
      "register": "registerLifeosPhase3Routes",
      "enabled": true,
      "note": "LifeOS Phase 3 REST (habits/energy/learning/calendar-protection). s7 blocked on missing auto-register after builder wrote broken sN-*-service imports — conductor GAP-FILL rewired to real lifeos-* services + mounted here."
    },
    {
      "path": "routes/tc-intake-routes.js",
      "register": "registerTcIntakeRoutes",
      "enabled": false,
      "note": "TC Service intake run + runs list. s10 false-done had reused an unrelated LifeOS auto-register commit; conductor GAP-FILL adds the real entries so module-health can pass. Disabled 2026-07-10: superseded by camelCase .mjs queue targets (step-08/09) to avoid double-mount."
    },
    {
      "path": "routes/tc-billing-routes.js",
      "register": "registerTcBillingRoutes",
      "enabled": false,
      "note": "TC Service billing checkout/enroll/webhook. Mounted via auto-register for founder-lane module-health. Disabled 2026-07-10: superseded by camelCase .mjs queue targets (step-08/09) to avoid double-mount."
    },
    {
      "path": "routes/tc-imap-routes.js",
