      "register": "registerMarketingYoutubeRoutes",
      "enabled": true,
      "note": "MarketingOS Phase 6 YouTube connect flow — ONE shared Google OAuth app (reuses GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID/SECRET already live for Calendar), per-client one-time consent via Google's own real login page. Exposes GET /api/v1/marketing/youtube/connect (redirect to Google), GET /.../callback (token exchange, stored in the existing user_integrations table under provider 'youtube_channel'), GET /.../status. Built by the loop (queued mos-youtube-connect-routes); mounted here so the functional-proof gate verifies the endpoints are LIVE before the step can be done. Records a benign 'module not found' health error until the loop ships the file — fail-open, never blocks boot."
