    },
    {
      "path": "routes/lifeos-member-feedback-routes.js",
      "register": "registerMemberFeedbackRoutes",
      "enabled": true,
      "note": "LifeOS member feedback REST surface. Auto-register entry added so the governed factory can ship the route and module-health can prove it LIVE."
    },
    {
      "path": "routes/lifeos-perfect-day-routes.js",
      "register": "registerLifeosPerfectDayRoutes",
      "enabled": true,
      "note": "LifeOS Perfect Day REST surface: plan, rate, re-prioritize, and ADD-style reminders. Auto-register entry added so the governed factory can ship the route and module-health can prove it LIVE."
    },
    {
      "path": "routes/marketing-community-value-routes.js",
      "register": "registerMarketingCommunityValueRoutes",
      "enabled": true
    },
    {
      "path": "routes/marketing-session-export-routes.js",
      "register": "registerMarketingSessionExportRoutes",
      "enabled": true,
      "note": "GAP-FILL: built (BUILD_QUEUE mos-session-export/mos-r2-upload) but never auto-registered, so it stayed unreachable through 3 verify attempts. Also fixed on the same pass: the route's own local buildSessionExport/uploadAudioToR2 reimplementations never called the real services/marketing-session-export.js and services/marketing-r2-upload.js built alongside them in the same session (the R2 upload path asked an AI council member to fabricate a URL instead of doing a real S3/R2 PutObject), and the auth check used req.session.userId even though this codebase has no express-session middleware anywhere, so it would 401 every request unconditionally. Swapped to deps.requireKey, the pattern every other auto-registered route already uses."
